287:- 2026-04-24 [mypy] `**ignore_missing_imports = true` does NOT silence `Library stubs not installed` errors** for modules mypy knows have published stubs (yaml, jsonschema). Fix is either `pip install types-PyYAML types-jsonschema` in the dev extra, or a per-module override with `follow_imports = "skip"`. Did both so CI is robust whether or not the dev extra is installed.
311:- 2026-04-26 [sdk][ksm][bootstrap] **`dsk bootstrap-ksm` is the production on-ramp; without it KSM-as-SDK-feature has a four-step manual prefix.** Adopters won't actually use `KsmLoginHelper` if the prerequisite (KSM app + admin-record share + redeemed config on disk) requires Web UI clicks. Bootstrap collapses (a) app-create-or-reuse, (b) admin-record-create-or-share, (c) one-time-token generation, (d) token redemption + config write, (e) verification, into one Commander-driven invocation. Idempotency matters: re-running with the same `--app-name` reuses the existing app rather than creating a duplicate; same for `--with-bus` directory record by title. `--login-helper {commander,ksm,/path}` lets bootstrap drive itself once initial bootstrap landed (rotate clients without a fresh interactive login). All Commander calls wrapped in `redirect_stdout`/`redirect_stderr` so tokens never reach stdout. `CapabilityError(context=partial)` on every failure carries `app_uid` / `record_uid` / `config_path` so the operator can copy-paste cleanup commands from the next-action.
316:- 2026-04-26 [sdk][handoff] **A handoff card replaces a handoff conversation.** "Finish it all for a new agent to take over" is not "do everything pending"; it's "leave the next agent a single document that lets them decide what to do without re-reading the transcript". Shape: branch state + per-track next-action (concrete, with file pointers) + verify commands that should pass on first turn + hardening reminders the next agent will otherwise relearn. Anti-patterns: (a) listing pending tracks without next-actions ("Phase B bus" alone is useless), (b) carrying forward phantom symbols without grounding ("Wave-1B `_resolve_project_tree`" turned out to not exist anywhere — verify with grep before listing), (c) prose paragraphs where bullets work. The new agent's first two messages should be: read handoff card, run verify commands. If either fails, the handoff was wrong and the originating agent owes a follow-up.
351:- 2026-04-26 [codex-sandbox][shared-object-store] **Linked worktrees need TWO directories writable beyond the cwd, not one: the per-worktree gitdir (`<primary>/.git/worktrees/<n>/`) AND the common gitdir (`<primary>/.git/`).** First fix patched `codex_offline.sh` to add only the per-worktree gitdir from `git rev-parse --git-dir`; workers immediately hit a second `Operation not permitted` writing blobs to `<primary>/.git/objects/`. The common gitdir holds the shared object store + refs that every linked worktree commits into. Final fix: also auto-add `git rev-parse --git-common-dir` (with dedup when equal to per-worktree gitdir for normal clones). Pattern: when sandbox-tightening blocks ANY git operation in a linked worktree, the answer is always BOTH gitdirs (`--git-dir` + `--git-common-dir`); a partial fix that only adds one is a recurring failure mode that re-bites at the next operation. Verified by 3 cov slices (redact, schema, normalize) all landing successfully via parent-commit in the same session — workers only need to be re-launched if the deliverable itself is wrong, not if the tooling layer is busted.
