368:- 2026-04-26 [codex-cli][bg-detach] **Background launchers must use `nohup` + runner-script + redirect-from-/dev/null, not `( ... ) &`.** Cursor's Shell tool starts a fresh bash per command that exits when the command returns. Naive `( ... ) &` subshells inherit that bash as their parent and catch SIGHUP when it exits — the cleanup block (writing `STATE=DONE` to the marker) never runs. First version of `codex_offline_bg.sh` had this bug; bus.py worker completed a clean READONLY-OK memo in the log but the marker stayed `LAUNCHED` forever. Fix: write the codex command + cleanup into a runner script (`/tmp/codex-offline-<ts>-<pid>.runner.sh`) and launch via `nohup bash $RUNNER </dev/null >/dev/null 2>&1 &`. `disown` alone is not enough on macOS bash inside an exiting parent. Verified: trivial test prompt now writes `STATE=DONE EXIT_CODE=0` correctly within seconds of codex finishing.
