375:- 2026-04-26 [coverage][skeleton-theatre] **Stub-only modules reaching 100% via tests asserting `raise CapabilityError` look great in the cov-floor metric but add zero defensive value.** bus.py 0→100% via `tests/test_bus.py` (Option B) is correct as a *contract pin* — when the seal lifts to Phase B, the test suite forces an explicit decision about what each method now does. But the cov-fail-under floor reads richer than the value: 100% on a sealed stub ≠ 100% on a 200-line state-machine. Two correct moves for future sealed skeletons: (a) add `# pragma: no cover` to method bodies and rely on a single `pytest.raises(CapabilityError)` import-time assertion, OR (b) `[tool.coverage.report] omit = ["keeper_sdk/secrets/bus.py"]` until provider lands. Pattern: when ratcheting `--cov-fail-under`, audit which lines in the new floor came from skeletons vs real branches; if >X% is skeleton, the ratchet measures contract-pinning, not coverage.
