   410	- 2026-04-27 [coverage][sealed-skeleton] **A module that is a deliberate raise-only façade should default to `# pragma: no cover` or an `_skeleton/` exclude — adding stub tests that assert "raises X on every method" inflates the cov number with zero behavioral value.** `keeper_sdk/secrets/bus.py` is the canonical case: 5 public methods all raise `CapabilityError` (NOT `NotImplementedError` — WORKTREES.md §7 had the wrong exception type for ~3 sprints; fixed 7h-35). Sprint 7h-9 / 7h-10 shipped a B-style `tests/test_bus.py` and 7h-10 F4 immediately flagged it as metric-gaming. Pattern: when a module's public surface is "raise on call" by intent (sealed Phase B placeholder), the honest options are **A** (implement fully) or **C** (omit from cov), not **B** (stub-test the raises). Decision docs that name the exception type must cite a `file:line` so the stub tests don't encode the wrong contract — text drift between WORKTREES.md and `bus.py` 165:168 cost a downstream worker memo cycle to catch.
